    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-02-19T18:47:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-02-19T18:47:00-05:00" n="4"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d4">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.5 <gloss target="#t_MSP1">MSP</gloss>/2 1352:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 4<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Legation in Switzerland</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d4fn1">Drafted by <persName>Vance</persName> and <persName
                            corresp="#p_LYONSDM1">Lyons</persName>, cleared with <persName
                            corresp="#p_CAMPM1">Camp</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_DULLESJF1"
                            >Foster</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_RONHOVDEAG1"
                            >Ronhovde</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_BYINGTONHMJ1"
                            >Byington</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_ALLENWD1">Allen</persName>,
                            <persName>Scott</persName>, <persName>Dawson</persName>, <persName
                            corresp="#p_KAPLANJ1">Kaplan</persName>, and <persName
                            corresp="#p_GORDONL1">Gordon</persName>, and repeated for action to
                        Vienna and Stockholm and for infomation to London and Paris.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-02-19T18:47:00-05:00"
                            >February 19, 1952—6:47 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1081. Re Bern’s 1005, rptd London 71, Paris 88, which being rptd Vienna and
                        Stockholm.<note n="2" xml:id="d4fn2">Not printed; in it Ambassador <persName
                            corresp="#p_PATTERSONRC1">Patterson</persName> warned the Department of
                        State that Switzerland would withdraw from <gloss target="#t_OEEC1"
                            >OEEC</gloss> if it became the economic arm of <gloss target="#t_NATO1"
                            >NATO</gloss>. He stated that Switzerland does not object too strongly
                        to covert cooperation between <gloss target="#t_OEEC1">OEEC</gloss> and
                            <gloss target="#t_NATO1">NATO</gloss> but would leave <gloss
                            target="#t_OEEC1">OEEC</gloss> if the cooperation was brought too far
                        into the open. (740.5 <gloss target="#t_MSP1">MSP</gloss>/2–1352)</note>
                </p>
                <p>Dept does not desire modify <gloss target="#t_NATO1">NATO</gloss>–<gloss
                        target="#t_OEEC1">OEEC</gloss> relationship in manner which wld result in
                    withdrawal Switz, Austria, or Sweden from <gloss target="#t_OEEC1">OEEC</gloss>
                    and <gloss target="#t_Todep1">Todep</gloss> 560, rptd Paris 4723<note n="3"
                        xml:id="d4fn3">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note> shld be so construed (<gloss
                        target="#t_Todep1">Todep</gloss> 560, on which Depintel Feb 12 based being
                    rptd Vienna, Stockholm, Bern). What Dept has in mind is that work of <gloss
                        target="#t_OEEC1">OEEC</gloss> if it is to be realistic must necessarily
                    take into account econ impact of defense effort and that much of what <gloss
                        target="#t_OEEC1">OEEC</gloss> does can make contribution to <gloss
                        target="#t_NATO1">NATO</gloss>. Relationship with <gloss target="#t_NATO1"
                        >NATO</gloss> wld remain on informal basis and autonomy and independence
                        <gloss target="#t_OEEC1">OEEC</gloss> preserved. Essential prob is one of
                    clarification usefulness <gloss target="#t_OEEC1">OEEC</gloss> rather than basic
                    change.</p>
                <p>Bern, Vienna and Stockholm pls comment on probable reactions <gloss
                        target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> to proposed relationship.</p>
                <p>Dep desires avoid on one hand conflict and duplication efforts and on other hand
                    eventual atrophy <gloss target="#t_OEEC1">OEEC</gloss> and consequent narrowing
                    of geographic area of coop.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_WEBBJE1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Webb</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
